BANGKOK
DONG KINGMAN
BANGKOK
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.
Among the 300 splendid temples in Bangkok, the most famous are: the Temple of the Emerald
Buddha, Temple of the Reclining Buddha, Temple of the Golden Buddha and the Temple of the Dawn.
The exotic oriental ambiance is heightened by the saffron robed monks seen everywhere and the
traditional classical dancing. Here one can dine on the best rice in the world temptingly prepared
and laced with curry
The thoughtful service and gracious accommodations offered by the luxurious Siam
Inter-Continental are especially atuned to international travelers.
Bangkok is served by Pan Am on its Round-the-World flights
